{"type":"message","id":"4e5726f8","parentId":"ddf63e4e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:04:02.143Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ot5qbftkujau_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5613\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1899\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 040325 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1 advancement. It requires analyzing existing pulse logs to classify invariant vs variant content and predict next pulse from invariants. No TIC implementation exists yet.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"oceanic-shore","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5613\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1899\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 040325 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1 advancement. It requires analyzing existing pulse logs to classify invariant vs variant content and predict next pulse from invariants. No TIC implementation exists yet.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774339442141}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba2645a0","parentId":"4e5726f8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:04:02.146Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ot5qbftkujau_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 040014\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- Key insight: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the same problem\r\n- Next action: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement TIC on the last 20 pulse logs in `logs/pulse_*.md`.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. First understand what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Implement the TIC classifier\r\n3. Create a test script that processes the logs\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available and create the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the last 20 pulse log files\r\n2. Implements basic temporal invariance compression (classifying content as invariant vs variant)\r\n3. Tests prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me create this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a clear path forward: implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment to test whether invariant discovery predicts next-pulse content. I need to build a classifier that processes the pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `experiments/tic_experiment.ps1` - a PowerShell script that reads recent pulse logs, implements basic temporal invariance classification, and tests prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$MaxLogs = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogsDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\r\n$script:invariantScore = 0\r\n$script:variantScore = 0\r\n$script:predictionScore = 0\r\n\r\nfunction Get-TemporalInvariants {\r\n    param([string[]]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants: patterns that persist across sessions\r\n    # - Goal references (Phase, pending, completed)\r\n    # - Architecture mentions (Compositional, TemporalAttention, Infant)\r\n    # - Key insights (gap, compression, λ parameter)\r\n    \r\n    $invariantPatterns = @(\r\n        \"Phase \\d\", \"COMPLETE\", \"PENDING\", \"Architecture\",\r\n        \"gap.*decay\", \"compression\", \"TemporalAttention\",\r\n        \"Invariant\", \"Causal\", \"session\", \"pulse\"\r\n    )\r\n    \r\n    $variantPatterns = @(\r\n        \"OBSERVATION\", \"ACTION\", \"MUTATION\", \"old_text:\", \"new_text:\",\r\n        \"timestamp\", \"^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}\"\r\n    )\r\n    \r\n    $contentStr = $Content -join \" \"\r\n    $invariants = 0\r\n    $variants = 0\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($pattern in $invariantPatterns) {\r\n        if ($contentStr -match $pattern) { $invariants++ }\r\n    }\r\n    foreach ($pattern in $variantPatterns) {\r\n        if ($contentStr -match $pattern) { $variants++ }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Invariants = $invariants\r\n        Variants = $variants\r\n        Total = $invariants + $variants\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Get-NextPulsePrediction {\r\n    param([string[]]$CurrentContent, [string[]]$NextContent)\r\n    \r\n    # Prediction: next pulse should maintain invariants, update variants\r\n    $current = Get-TemporalInvariants -Content $CurrentContent\r\n    $next = Get-TemporalInvariants -Content $NextContent\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants should persist (reconstruction of persistent state)\r\n    $invariantRecall = if ($current.Invariants -gt 0) { $next.Invariants / $current.Invariants } else { 0 }\r\n    \r\n    # Variants should differ (fresh reconstruction adds new context)\r\n    $variantNovelty = if ($current.Variants -gt 0) { ($next.Variants -ne $current.Variants) ? 1 : 0 } else { 0 }\r\n    \r\n    return ($invariantRecall + $variantNovelty) / 2\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Main experiment\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Testing compression-causal duality on pulse logs...`n\"\r\n\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $MaxLogs\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 2) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient pulse logs ($($pulseFiles.Count) found, need 2+)\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n$classificationCorrect = 0\r\n$predictionResults = @()\r\n\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt ($pulseFiles.Count - 1); $i++) {\r\n    $current = Get-Content $pulseFiles[$i].FullName -Raw\r\n    $next = Get-Content $pulseFiles[$i+1].FullName -Raw\r\n    \r\n    $currentAnalysis = Get-TemporalInvariants -Content ($current -split \"`n\")\r\n    $nextAnalysis = Get-TemporalInvariants -Content ($next -split \"`n\")\r\n    \r\n    # Classification: higher invariant ratio = more causal structure\r\n    $ratio = if ($currentAnalysis.Total -gt 0) { \r\n        $currentAnalysis.Invariants / $currentAnalysis.Total \r\n    } else { 0\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 2\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:00:47\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774339442143}}
