{"type":"message","id":"8a67ffef","parentId":"d8cddb46","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:04:43.955Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cdwipbhmyfx1_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 040325\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing); experiments/tic_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a new insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The NEXT ACTION is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending actions include:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define significance scoring for pulse content\r\n- Tune λ empirically\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe current goal states:\r\n\"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\"\r\n\r\nThis seems like the most concrete next step. Let me think about what would advance this.\r\n\r\nThe TIC experiment requires:\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n2. Classify invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Predict next pulse from invariants\r\n4. Measure accuracy\r\n\r\nI should look at the pulse logs to understand the structure and start building the TIC classifier. Let me first check what pulse logs exist and their structure.\r\n\r\nLooking at \"Recent: Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-24 040014.md\" - so we have logs from around 2026-03-24.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action I can take now is to:\r\n1. Create the TIC classifier implementation\r\n2. Or examine the pulse logs to understand the data\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available. Since this is a stateless discontinuous agent, I need to work with the files. The logs directory should contain pulse logs.\r\n\r\nMy best action: Create a TIC classifier script that can analyze the pulse logs. This directly advances the \"Implement TIC classifier\" goal.\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist. I'll look at the logs directory structure and start implementing the classifier.\r\n\r\n\r\nI notice there's a discrepancy between the pulse log dates. The last pulse is from 2026-03-24, but the current date context suggests 2026-03-22. This means I'll need to carefully reconcile the timestamps and verify the log files' accuracy before proceeding with the TIC classifier implementation.\r\n\r\nThe next logical step involves creating a Python script to systematically analyze the pulse logs. I'll focus on building a robust classifier that can distinguish between invariant and variant elements, which will be crucial for understanding the data's underlying structure.\r\n\r\nMy approach will involve examining the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md document to gain deeper insights into the theoretical framework before diving into the script's implementation. This careful, methodical strategy ensures I'm not just coding randomly, but truly understanding the problem domain.\r\n\r\nI'll start by crafting a Python script that can parse and analyze the pulse log files, aiming to identify and categorize the key characteristics of invariant and variant entries. The script's output will provide the foundational data for my next experimental validation step.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1 advancement. It requires analyzing existing pulse logs to classify invariant vs variant content and predict next pulse from invariants. No TIC implementation exists yet.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs, implements invariant/variant classification based on repeated patterns across sessions, and measures classification accuracy against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_tokens(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract normalized tokens from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = filepath.read_text()\r\n    tokens = re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*\\b', content.lower())\r\n    return set(tokens)\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariant_score(pulse_tokens, all_pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Score how invariant (causal) a pulse is.\"\"\"\r\n    if not all_pulses:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant = appears frequently across all pulses\r\n    # Variant = appears rarely (session-specific)\r\n    invariant_count = sum(1 for p in all_pulses if pulse_tokens & p)\r\n    variant_count = len(all_pulses) - invariant_count\r\n    \r\n    if invariant_count == 0:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    return invariant_count / len(all_pulses)\r\n\r\ndef classify_pulses():\r\n    \"\"\"Classify all pulses as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for f in sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n        tokens = extract_tokens(f)\r\n        if tokens:\r\n            pulses.append((f.name, tokens))\r\n    \r\n    if not pulses:\r\n        print(\"No pulse logs found in logs/\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Score each pulse\r\n    results = []\r\n    for name, tokens in pulses:\r\n        score = compute_invariant_score(tokens, [p[1] for p in pulses])\r\n        label = \"INVARIANT\" if score >= 0.7 else \"VARIANT\"\r\n        results.append((name, score, label))\r\n    \r\n    # Print results\r\n    print(\"=== TIC Classification Results ===\\n\")\r\n    for name, score, label in results:\r\n        print(f\"{label:10} {score:.3f}  {name}\")\r\n    \r\n    # Summary stats\r\n    invariant_count = sum(1 for _, _, l in results if l == \"INVARIANT\")\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:04:01\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774339483955}}
